"To the communist cause!"

50
00:02:06,409 --> 00:02:09,609
"Love the people!"

51
00:02:09,609 --> 00:02:15,629
Yeah...communism is all about...loving...the
people.

52
00:02:15,629 --> 00:02:19,879
I guess these “red nobility” have such
a rosy view of history,

53
00:02:19,879 --> 00:02:22,139
they might have missed the bloodshed.

54
00:02:22,580 --> 00:02:23,880
“Life has improved so much that children

55
00:02:23,889 --> 00:02:27,549
can’t understand the hardship of those who
built our country.”

56
00:02:27,549 --> 00:02:29,380
Right, professor.

57
00:02:29,380 --> 00:02:31,480
Like all of the adults in the school do.

58
00:02:31,480 --> 00:02:34,959
I mean, you weren’t around back then either.

59
00:02:34,959 --> 00:02:38,019
You may have been a child during the Cultural
Revolution,

60
00:02:38,019 --> 00:02:39,239
when schools were shut down

61
00:02:39,239 --> 00:02:41,689
so kids could play with guns.

62
00:02:41,689 --> 00:02:44,780
But those were Cultural Revolution Red Guards.

63
00:02:44,780 --> 00:02:47,909
These kids are dressing up like the Red Army.

64
00:02:47,909 --> 00:02:50,269
And what do they want to do when they grow
up?

65
00:02:50,269 --> 00:02:54,319
“I want to be a doctor in the future”

66
